City crime data summary

The data for New York included in the Crime Open Database (CODE) includes records for 5,493,678 offences between 2007 and 2017.

Excluded cases

Cases are excluded from the final dataset for various reasons. Overall 238,566 (4% of the total) cases have been excluded.

This leaves a total of 5,255,112 geniune cases included in the data.

Spatial distribution

city_outline <- st_read(paste0("../spatial_data/cities/tl_2016_", 
                               cities$fips[cities$name == this_city], 
                               "_place.shp"), quiet = TRUE) %>% 
  filter(NAME == this_city)
city_bbox <- st_bbox(city_outline)

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = tigris::states(year = 2016, class = "sf"), 
          fill = NA, colour = "#999999") +
  geom_hex(
    mapping = aes(x = longitude, y = latitude),
    data = filter(data, !is.na(latitude) & !is.na(longitude)),
    bins = 50
  ) +
  geom_sf(
    data = city_outline, fill = NA
  ) +
  lims(x = c(city_bbox$xmin, city_bbox$xmax), 
       y = c(city_bbox$ymin, city_bbox$ymax)) +
  scale_fill_continuous(low = "#FFFFFF", high = "#000000", 
                        label = scales::comma) +
  labs(title = "Spatial distribution of crimes", subtitle = "all offences", 
       x = "", y = "") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_line(colour = "#CCCCCC")
  )

Crime types

Offenses in the CODE data are split into three categories: crimes against people, property and society. These categories are then split into smaller categories for different offense types.

if (length(missing_types) > 0) {

Some types of crime are missing from the New York data:

  • 26d Welfare Fraud
  • 36a Incest
  • 36b Statutory Rape
  • 39d Sports Tampering
  • 64a Human Trafficking, Commercial Sex Acts
  • 64b Human Trafficking, Involuntary Servitude
  • 90e Drunkenness (Except Driving Under The Influence)
  • 90g Liquor Law Violations (Except Driving Under The Influence And Drunkenness)
  • 90h Peeping Tom
other_cats <- data %>% 
  filter(str_sub(offense_code, 3, 3) == "U") %>% 
  mutate(Type = paste(offense_code, offense_type)) %>% 
  group_by(Type) %>% 
  summarise(Cases = n()) %>% 
  mutate(Cases = format(Cases, big.mark = ","))

if (nrow(other_cats) > 0) {
